rating_comment: Nikhil and his family were awesome hosts. They even gave dinner on some days, walked me to the temple and Nikhil insisted on helping with my bags and waiting until my driver arrived with me, at 01.00 am. I felt very much at home and will definitely be back.
Nikhil place was very good place to stay and Mataji and Parvuji was very helpful and polite.

Very nice, clean room with AC. Beautiful view from the balcony. Nikhil's mother is a super kind mataji. The Iskcon temple is just a short walk from the flat.
Highly recommend!
comfy stay. Great location. Nikhil communicates as well as any expectations I could have of a good host.

I'm here to write about Nikhil's family, they made us feel included. The food and hospitality are just awesome. That Herbal tea pizza is mouthwatering. Especially Sneha not only took good care of us and also showed us belongingness. This is true Airbnb accommodation and they are just fabulous Hosts. Whenever I visit Mayapur will stay at their place though lift is a bit of concern, however when you have such a loving family rest can be ignored. 5 star from every aspect.

Pros : location, cleanliness, homely, supportive, good view of temple, balcony.
Can be improved : Table, Lift, cupboard utility, towel and facilitate morning tea
The charges are on higher side vis a vis the amenities.
